deck: The youngest of the paper sisters
description:
Powers and Abilities

Of the paper sisters Anita is the most focused on offense she can mold paper into sharp blades often for increasing her potential in close range combat. She can throw sheets of paper for a shuriken like attack as well. For defense she is much weaker than the other paper masters shown since to block a bullet she required a book instead of a single sheet such as Yumiko. Anita is an excellent hand to hand combatant and his very agile and flexible. Her toes are particularly strong and she can often hang from them, tear paper, or grab a knife solely with her toes.
name: Anita King

description:
Powers and Abilities

Of the paper sisters, Maggie is easily the most focused on defense. Her primary ability is to form paper familiars, who look like animals in order to attack, defend, or for travel. The volume of her control allows her to make a paper bird that is larger than a typical commercial aircraft. She is quite good and forming shields and barriers for defense. The volume of her creations means she probably is the most powerful of the three paper sisters. This is proven in the anime when she fights Sonny Wong (the most powerful paper master shown) one on one to by her sisters time.
name: Maggie Mui

description:
Powers and abilities

Michelle is the leader of the paper sisters and often plays the support role at long range. She often forms a longbow and arrow with her paper mastery and can change her arrow to have specific effects such as forming a net or hiding something else inside the arrow.
name: Michelle Cheung

deck: Paradox Girl is a young woman with the power to teleport through time and space at will. She can summon any number of temporal duplicates, but often works at cross-purposes with herself, her powers causing her problems as well as solving them. She is part of a duo with Axiom Man.
description:
Origin

Her constant interference in her own timeline means that she has several different origins and is never entirely sure which one is currently true. Similarly, she no longer remembers the source of her powers, the circumstances of her birth, or even her own name.
